dataLineage.statement:
Layer was sent to ITOS as a zipped shapefile in an email from UNOCHA. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS: 1. As requested by UNOCHA, Admin1 name "South West Ethiopia Peoples'" was changed to "South West Ethiopia". 2. Admin1 name "Harar" changed to "Harari" to match Admin3 attribution. 3. Admin1 name "Benishangul Gumuz" changed to "Benishangul Gumz" to match Admin3 attribution.
The following was found by ITOS but not addressed in this version: 1. The slashes and parentheses in some names suggest the presence of alternate names that should be separated and placed in an AltName field
